data.content:
user
The 'user' table stores information about users, including their unique identifiers and personal details such as usernames, passwords, and email addresses.

user_region
The 'user_region' table contains geographical location data for users, detailing their coordinates, province, city, district, and the associated user's ID.

article
The 'article' table is designed to hold information about articles, including title, content, publication date, user ID of the author, and metrics like clicks and dissent counts.

id
The 'id' field in various tables acts as a unique identifier and primary key for records, allowing for individual recognition of entries.

username
The 'username' field represents the name chosen by the user for their account, serving as a public identifier.

password
The 'password' field stores the user's secret access code for account protection and authentication.

email
The 'email' field is provided by users for communication and account recovery purposes.

icon
The 'icon' field links to the user's profile picture, representing their visual identity on the platform.

coin_num
The 'coin_num' field indicates the amount of virtual currency the user possesses, which may be used for various transactions.

join_time
The 'join_time' field captures the timestamp of when the user registered on the platform.

admin
The 'admin' field distinguishes users with administrative privileges from regular users, indicated by a binary value.

jing_du
The 'jing_du' field represents the longitudinal coordinate of a user's geographic location.

wei_du
The 'wei_du' field represents the latitudinal coordinate of a user's geographic location.

province
The 'province' field indicates the administrative division of a user's location, providing regional context.

city
The 'city' field specifies the urban locality of the user's residence.

district
The 'district' field further refines the user's location down to a smaller administrative sector within the city.

name
The 'name' field denotes the specific location name that is associated with a user's geographic data.

user_id
The 'user_id' field serves as a foreign key that links geographic data back to the corresponding user in the 'user' table.

title
The 'title' field is the headline or main name of an article, summarizing its content.

content
The 'content' field contains the main body text or information of the article, detailing the subject matter.

pdatetime
The 'pdatetime' field records the date and time when the article was published.

type_id
The 'type_id' field categorizes articles based on predefined types or classifications.

click_num
The 'click_num' field counts how many times the article has been viewed, indicating its popularity.

disagree
The 'disagree' field tracks the number of times users have expressed disagreement with the article's content, reflecting its reception.

pic
The 'pic' field contains a link to an image associated with the article, enhancing its visual engagement.
